

###############
videkah AKA VimIDE
###############

a vim ide.
############################
by Karl Khaos Hoskin
Feb 2014
############################


###########################################################
~/.vim/videkah/project_config/
########

stores the base_dirs of projects.

i.e.

~/.vim/videkah/project_config/no1_proj

will contain the following lines , which could be something like :-

BASE_DIR=/home/myuser/git-co/my_no1_proj/
FILELIST_BY=by_git_branch
# above could be either by_git_branch, by_path, by_path_n_git_branch , local where :-

(1) by_git_branch
(2) by_path
(3) by_path_n_git_branch
(4) local



###########################################################
~/.vim/videkah/filelists/<project_name>/

stores the filelists for the various different ways filelists are stored by.


###########################################################
~/.vim/videkah/runlists/<project_name>/


stores ther runlists

###########################################################

~/.vim/videkah/bin/

stores all the binaries / scripts.







############################################################



has a list of files

the list of files are saved in ~/.vim/filelists/<file>


navigates stack traces. firstly perl stack traces , maybe other ones too.





by path config.
##############

when it opens it checks the pwd.

this tells it what config to use,
and where the "filelist" is.
is it in :-
1) ~/.vim/videkah/filelists/by-git-branch/

2) ~/.vim/videkah/filelists/by-path/

3) ~/.vim/videkah/filelists/by-path-n-git-branch/




~/.vim/videkah/bin/

    videkah shell script
    perlstacktrace.pl



generalised , a perl module/project somewhere config.


Runlists
########

list of external shell scripts that can be run.



stacktrace
##########
stacktrace navigating buffer.


